# ── Frontend env (Vite build-time) ────────────────────────────────────
#
# DistroMap ships full-stack on ONE Vercel project with `frontend/` as
# the project root. The suggestion API is a TypeScript serverless
# function at `api/index.ts` (Vercel `@vercel/node` runtime), and
# `vercel.json` rewrites `/api/(.*) → /api/index` so the SPA and the
# API share the same origin. No separate backend host is needed — and
# no Python venv either, the whole stack is TypeScript/Node.
#
# VITE_API_URL is OPTIONAL and normally LEFT UNSET:
#   - In dev:    unset → the Vite dev server serves /api/* in-process
#                via the apiServerPlugin in vite.config.js. One command
#                (`npm run dev`), one process, one port (:5173).
#   - In prod:   unset → requests go to same-origin /api/* on Vercel,
#                which the rewrite routes to the Node function.
#
# Only set VITE_API_URL if you move the API to a DIFFERENT host
# (e.g. during migration testing). Trailing slash is tolerated.
#
# Example (NOT recommended for normal Vercel deploys):
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com/api

VITE_API_URL=

# ── Backend env (read by api/index.ts at runtime, not Vite) ───────────
#
# Vercel auto-injects these when you link a KV store from the project
# dashboard → Storage → Create Database → KV. They switch the API
# from local file mode to Upstash Redis REST mode. In file mode
# (local dev) the API writes to frontend/.cache/api/suggestions.json.
#
# DO NOT commit real values. Set them in the Vercel dashboard or via
# `vercel env add`. They are listed here only as documentation.
#
#   KV_REST_API_URL=
#   KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
#
# Optional: comma-separated extra CORS origins (custom domains, LAN IPs).
#   ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://distromap.com,https://www.distromap.com
